# .driftignore — patterns the vault-repo drift check should NOT flag.
#
# Copy this to `.driftignore` in your repo clone (it's gitignored locally so
# your personal patterns never get committed):
#
#     cp .driftignore.example .driftignore
#
# One pattern per line. Matched as a substring against the path the drift
# check emits (e.g. `rules/voice-style.md`, `scripts/audit-foo.py`,
# `skills/my-private-skill`, `hooks/my-business.sh`).
#
# Add a pattern when an item is permanently personal: tied to your name,
# your company, your psychological framework, your domain, or your private
# workflow. Generic patterns are universal and should be contributed
# upstream as PRs instead.

# --- Examples (delete or edit) ---
# rules/my-voice-style.md
# rules/my-company-brand-guide.md
# scripts/my-business-digest.sh
# skills/my-private-skill
# hooks/my-business.sh

# --- Patterns that are universal-personal and always safe to ignore ---
# (uncomment if you don't want them flagged)
# scripts/__pycache__
